{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/learning-disabilities/how-this-topic-was-developed/evidence-exclusion-criteria/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"99791e8d-d65b-573e-8907-07ff851cb6a2","slug":"evidence-exclusion-criteria","fullItemName":"Evidence exclusion criteria","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 494c90c5-3164-4431-928a-a8e200bd4669 --><h2>Evidence exclusion criteria</h2><!-- end field 494c90c5-3164-4431-928a-a8e200bd4669 -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 1c56f0e9-6bb4-40fb-827e-a8e200bd4669 --><!-- begin field 3635f474-00c2-4dba-8899-a8e200bd4669 --><h2>Our policy</h2><!-- end field 3635f474-00c2-4dba-8899-a8e200bd4669 --><!-- begin field 58de4e13-aafc-4546-a144-a8e200bd4669 --><p>Scoping a literature search, and reviewing the evidence for CKS is a methodical and systematic process that is carried out by the lead clinical author for each topic. Relevant evidence is gathered in order that the clinical author can make fully informed decisions and recommendations. It is important to note that some evidence may be excluded for a variety of reasons. These reasons may be applied across all CKS topics or may be specific to a given topic.</p><p>Studies identified during literature searches are reviewed to identify the most appropriate information to author a CKS topic, ensuring any recommendations are based on the best evidence. We use the principles of the GRADE and PICOT approaches to assess the quality of published research. We use the principles of AGREE II to assess the quality of published guidelines.</p><!-- end field 58de4e13-aafc-4546-a144-a8e200bd4669 --><!-- begin field f55003c4-a4c0-4e85-a5d4-a8e200bd4669 --><h2>Standard exclusions for scoping literature:</h2><!-- end field f55003c4-a4c0-4e85-a5d4-a8e200bd4669 --><!-- begin field b584405d-b80d-4315-8c65-a8e200bd4669 --><ul><li>Animal studies</li><li>Original research is not written in English</li></ul><!-- end field b584405d-b80d-4315-8c65-a8e200bd4669 --><!-- begin field 478d3a20-d59d-4108-907f-a8e200bd4669 --><h2>Possible exclusions for reviewed literature:</h2><!-- end field 478d3a20-d59d-4108-907f-a8e200bd4669 --><!-- begin field 331931a7-7582-40b8-bda1-a8e200bd4669 --><ul><li>Sample size too small or study underpowered</li><li>Bias evident or promotional literature</li><li>Population not relevant</li><li>Intervention/treatment not relevant</li><li>Outcomes not relevant</li><li>Outcomes have no clear evidence of clinical effectiveness</li><li>Setting not relevant</li><li>Not relevant to UK</li><li>Incorrect study type</li><li>Review article</li><li>Duplicate reference</li></ul><!-- end field 331931a7-7582-40b8-bda1-a8e200bd4669 --><!-- end item 1c56f0e9-6bb4-40fb-827e-a8e200bd4669 -->","topic":{"id":"81b6bf13-1851-5aca-a415-deb2664fff5b","topicId":"9cc09e0b-a51c-445a-a0f0-a8e200bd3e76","topicName":"Learning disabilities","slug":"learning-disabilities","lastRevised":"Last revised in August 2020","chapters":[{"id":"433a4d95-fb0e-597f-886b-7a5bba677e2e","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"e6952a3b-5351-51c3-b34d-3ce4fd90e136","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"cd675bbe-842b-5eac-9101-92f52a07ffd0","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"42e6170c-2ad4-5c42-98b5-66bb0f315b56","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"cdef379f-d2ef-5c80-9644-6e1cb6864f2a","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"f8ff91d6-3a99-5f81-ab3e-b522150de1f1","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"dbf4d83d-021c-5c6c-8be4-5637c384ed7b","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals"},{"id":"73bb96cd-3d7f-50c7-8bd6-2c3f50a56d70","slug":"outcome-measures","fullItemName":"Outcome measures"},{"id":"4e9fbda8-d558-51be-9f50-16e404570513","slug":"audit-criteria","fullI